spanGrp.span: `I am Hainsar Phawa, when i was a child i used to watched the goat and later when i was a bit older i used to watched the cattles.'; .'
To nga u-Hainsar Phawa, sohmynting, hei-por yong nga i wa dang man o u-khynnah chare blang, ka wa ar man o u-rap chran o khajiak, chare masi o.

`I was about 7 years when i watched the cattle, i began ploughing, i ploughed for sometimes and rest for sometimes because i was tired.'; 'stiar (a mud partition in a paddy field which seperates one bed from another).'
Manda chare masi o m o kam wa ynniaw snem, sdang o u-loor masi, loor masi lh chibt chipor da ngiah o, chong o chong o chipor cha 'stiar hali, nei-t yen lai li-loor o.
`my father made a small plough for me as i cannot plough the land with big ones as the elder did.'; .'
Dang chna lyngkor u-pa ya nga da ka-khian ne ka wa ym yee o u-loor kam wa loor ki wa hh da ka-hh ka-lyngkor.
`time passed by as a cowboy, we lived on agriculture, we cultivated paddy, potato and we don't have the opportunity to go to school.'; .'
hynrei t nongchari, T nang slm ki-por nang hh chare masi dp nei-t t, nawa chare masi lh im hei-rp hei-riang, hei-pooh hei-dain ya ka-pynthor kba, t rp salah, dp nei-t u-lai skur lh ym yoh lad.
`because our parents were poor, we lived on agriculture only, during those times even our village is still full of jungle, forest and trees.'; .'
Katwa dang dooh ki-bei ki-pa, i im bait dooh hi rp hi khih, t kat ka-t ka-por t ka-ni ka-chnong sohmyntin yong i lh nang dooh ka-khloo ka-dein chei-ni ka wa dang joor ka-kseh.
`our village was still a jungle and muddy, there were no tar road as we have now, our elders pave stone in the way.'; .'
Ka-chnong lh dang khloo dang kteih, ym pu m surok, kamni dang du ka-kteih u-lai, dang siang ki wa hh da ki-moo u-wi u-wi sa ar tymbood luti.
`sideways were full of pig's waste, the only way is the paved stones, but time went by, there was a change, i don't remember the year in which we got a road from the block.'; .'

Charood dooh ka-ait sniang wa rbn, ym lait u-lai u-wan, du na jrong moo, t nang slm ki-por nang kylla, nang mih ki-snm nang kylla t ka-juk hadooh wa poi ki-snm tip ki-snm ym m u-kynmoo bha o i-tu wa sdang u-yoh surok na ka-block.
`I think it's the year 60 or 63 that we got a road from the block, when the road was constucted then the cars starts coming.'; .'
ki-snm ynruphaw, ynruphaw le kop de sdang u-yoh surok na ka-block, manda yoh surok na ka-block, t wan ki-kari ki-motor.
`the cars came and brought us goods like timber, and we could sent our things to jowai and shillong as well.'; .'
Lait ki wan kit mar ya i chei-ni, kit dein kubit, i-won won i-jingmkam yoh u-kit cha jwai cha laban.

kam ki-yi ki-jait kari t i-por

T hadien nei-t da lai ki-t nei-bhah wan yn sa ki-ni ki-shaktiman ki-S-model ha ki-ni ki-juk ki wa katni, nei-t yn wan yn ki-ni ki-majarbus, wan kit bru ki, wan kmai ki cha ka-ni ka-chnong yong i.

ki-yi ki-jait ki-kari ki wa m nyngkong dooh ha ka-ni ka-chnong?

Ka-power wagon hei-yong i nga wa yah ka i-t i-por.

ha-o wa yah kari ha ka-ni ka-chnong.

cha ki-wi yn ki-chnong, wa marjan ne cha jwai da m kari da boon kari?

Dp yn t hawa wan yn tu ka-sngi yaw t wan ki-bus eh na khyriem, na laban, hei-sngi yaw jwai.

T ki-ni ki..? i-t por ki-ni ki-gmc lh dang duna ki toh m eh ka-wi ar tylli. Lh wa m eh kai u-tu u-kwin lamat na pasyih.
`all the people became christian since your childhood in this village'; .'
T hei-por dang khian phi mut da man kristan lut ki-bru waroh ha ka-ni ka-chnong mo?
`as far as i know know most people are christians since my childhood, non christian are found only in this locality loom pyrtooh.'; .'
Kat i-por wa dang khian o t kat kam wa tip o t da boon ki man kristan, du chei-ni ha loom pyrtooh wa dang man khasi ki-bru ym pu m u-man kristan.

`here in loom pyrtooh people started to convert into christianity since the coming of .'., all the people got .'., and since then conveted into christian they don't know anymore of the traditional belief.';.'
